-- Italy to Sign 2.4 Billion-Euro China Accords, Repubblica Says
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2010-10-07T06:47:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/italy-to-sign-3-4-billion-of-china-business-agreements-repubblica-says.html
Italy and China will sign business
agreements today valued at 2.43 billion euros ($3.4 billion),
daily la Repubblica reported, without saying where it got the
information.  The accords will include companies in the
telecommunications and renewable energy sectors, the daily
reported. Chinese President  Wen Jiabao  will meet members of the
Italian government today, including Prime Minister  Silvio Berlusconi , according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Armorel Kenna  in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  